你必须阻止他这么胡闹
You've got to stop him doing that.

244
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:08,710
他搞得我们像傻瓜
He's making us look like idiots.

245
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:11,390
要是你告诉我他怎么办到的 我会阻止他
If you can tell me how he does it, I'll stop him.

246
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,350
约翰
John!

247
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:25,710
约翰·华生
John Watson!

248
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,650
斯坦福，迈克·斯坦福，我们以前在巴茨医院共事
Stamford, Mike Stamford. We were at Barts together.

249
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:31,750
对，抱歉，迈克，你好
Yes, sorry, yes, Mike, hello.

250
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:34,330
- 没事，我理解，我胖了，  - 没有
- Yeah, I know, I got fat. - No, no.

251
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:37,070
我听说你到国外什么地方挨枪子儿去了，怎么回事？
I heard you were abroad somewhere getting shot at. What happened?

252
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:40,700
我中了枪
I got shot.

253
00:07:45,450 --> 00:07:47,010
那你还在巴茨医院吗
Are you still at Barts, then?

254
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:50,980
现在教书  阳光小青年，跟我们以前一样
Teaching now, yeah. Bright young things like we used to be.

255
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:52,830
老天  我讨厌他们
God, I hate them.

256
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,650
你呢？工作安顿之前，先住在城里吗？
What about you? Just staying in town till you get yourself sorted?

257
00:07:55,670 --> 00:07:57,570
靠军队退休金没法在伦敦过日子
I can't afford London on an Army pension.

258
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,690
你就是住其它地方也不行
You couldn't bear to be anywhere else.

259
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,980
那不是我认识的约翰·华生
That's not the John Watson I know.

260
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,670
对，我不是那个约翰·华生了
Yeah, I'm not the John Watson...

261
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,210
海瑞没帮上忙吗
Couldn't Harry help?

262
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,230
切，好像还有指望似的
Yeah, like that's going to happen

263
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:14,590
我不知道，找人合租之类呢？
I don't know, get a flatshare or something?

264
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:17,320
得了，谁愿意当我的室友？
Come on, who'd want me for a flatmate?

265
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:20,490
怎么了
What?

266
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:23,520
你是今天第二个跟我说这话的人
You're the second person to say that to me today.

267
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,270
第一个是谁？
Who was the first?

268
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:29,830
有多新鲜
How fresh?

269
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:32,630
刚刚送来  67岁  自然死亡
Just in. 67, natural causes.

270
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:35,830
以前在这工作，我认识他，人很好
Used to work here. I knew him, he was nice.

271
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:37,990
好
Fine.

272
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:40,270
我们先从短马鞭开始
We'll start with the riding crop.

273
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:53,870
今天不太顺，是吧
So, bad day, was it?

274
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:56,910
我要知道20分钟后的瘀伤形状
I need to know what bruises form in the next 20 minutes.

275
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
一个人的不在场证明就靠它了  发短信给我
A man's alibi depends on it. Text me.

276
00:08:59,570 --> 00:09:02,650
那个，我想问一下，也许等你工作完后…
Listen, I was wondering. Maybe later, when you're finished...

277
00:09:02,660 --> 00:09:04,650
你涂了唇膏，你刚才没涂唇膏啊
You're wearing lipstick. You weren't wearing lipstick before.

278
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:08,430
我...我稍微润色了一下
I, er... I refreshed it a bit.

279
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:11,110
不好意思，你刚才是说？
Sorry, you were saying?

280
00:09:11,850 --> 00:09:13,790
我是想问 你想喝咖啡吗
I was wondering if you'd like to have coffee.

281
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,590
清咖啡，两块糖，麻烦了，我就在楼上
Black, two sugars, please. I'll be upstairs.

282
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:20,110
好吧
Ok.

283
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:35,150
- 跟我那会儿有点不一样了  - 你都想不到
- Bit different from my day. - You've no idea!

284
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:37,600
迈克，能否借用你的电话，我的没信号
Mike, can I borrow your phone? There's no signal on mine.

285
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:40,500
- 固定电话有问题吗  - 我更喜欢发短信
- And what's wrong with the landline? - I prefer to text.

286
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:43,550
抱歉，在我大衣里
Sorry, it's in my coat.

287
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:47,270
哦，给，用我的吧
Er, here...use mine.

288
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:49,670
哦，谢谢
Oh, thank you.

289
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:52,510
这是我的一个老朋友，约翰·华生
This is an old friend of mine, John Watson.

290
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,310
阿富汗还是伊拉克？
Afghanistan or Iraq?

291
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:03,510
- 什么？  - 哪一个，阿富汗还是伊拉克？
- Sorry? - Which was it, in Afghanistan or Iraq?

292
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,350
阿富汗，不好意思，你怎么…
Afghanistan. Sorry, how did you...?

293
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,870
啊茉莉，咖啡，谢谢你
Ah, Molly, coffee, thank you.

294
00:10:11,450 --> 00:10:12,430
你的唇膏怎么没了
What happened to the lipstick?

295
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:14,380
我用着没效果
It wasn't working for me.

296
00:10:14,410 --> 00:10:16,020
真的？我倒觉得很有改善
Really? I thought it was a big improvement.

297
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:18,470
你的嘴现在看着太小
Your mouth's too small now.

298
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:20,110
好吧
Ok.

299
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:22,750
你对小提琴有何看法？
How do you feel about the violin?

300
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,100
抱歉，什么？
I'm sorry, what?

301
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:29,550
我在思考问题时会拉小提琴
I play the violin when I'm thinking

302
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,950
有时我会一连几天不说话
and sometimes I don't talk for days on end.

303
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:32,600
会让你心烦吗？
Would that bother you?

304
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:34,710
未来的室友应该彼此了解最坏的一面
Potential flatmates should know the worst about each other.

305
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:39,540
- 你…你和他说起过我吗  - 一个字也没有
- You told him about me? - Not a word.

306
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,330
那谁说过室友的事了？
Then who said anything about flatmates?

307
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:45,590
我说过，早上告诉迈克，我这人肯定很难找到室友
I did. Told Mike this morning I must be a difficult man to find a flatmate for.

308
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,630
现在他来了，刚过午餐
Now here he is, just after lunch,

309
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:50,550
带来一个老友，显然刚在阿富汗服完兵役回家
with an old friend clearly just home from military service in Afghanistan.

310
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:51,810
这不难推论
Wasn't a difficult leap.

311
00:10:52,650 --> 00:10:54,110
你怎么知道阿富汗的事
How did you know about Afghanistan?

312
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:56,350
我看中一处不错的小地方 在伦敦市中心
Got my eye on a nice little place in central London.

313
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:58,030
我们应该有能力负担
We ought to be able to afford it.

314
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,070
我们明天晚上在那里见，七点
We'll meet there tomorrow evening, seven o'clock.

315
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,190
抱歉  赶时间
Sorry, got to dash.

316
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,960
我想我把短马鞭忘在停尸间了
I think I left my riding crop in the mortuary.

317
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,590
就这样吗？
Is that it?

318
00:11:06,050 --> 00:11:07,510
什么就这样？
Is that what?

319
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:10,800
我们才刚见面  就要一起去看房了吗
We've only just met and we're going to go and look at a flat?

320
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,590
有问题吗
Problem?

321
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,730
我们一点也不了解对方
We don't know a thing about each other.

322
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:17,600
我不知道我们去哪里见
I don't know where we're meeting.

323
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:18,840
我甚至不知道你的名字
I don't even know your name.

324
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:21,920
我知道你是个军医
I know you're an Army doctor

325
00:11:21,930 --> 00:11:23,630
刚从阿富汗因伤退役回来
and you've been invalided home from Afghanistan.

326
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,160
我知道你有个兄弟担心你
I know you've got a brother worried about you,

327
00:11:25,170 --> 00:11:26,350
但你不向他求助
but you won't go to him for help

328
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,450
因为你看不惯他
because you don't approve of him,

329
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:28,990
可能因为他是酒鬼
possibly because he's an alcoholic,

330
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:31,390
更可能是因为他最近抛弃了自己的妻子
more likely because he recently walked out on his wife.

331
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,780
而且我知道  你的咨询师认为…
And I know your therapist thinks

332
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,990
你的跛腿是心理疾病，相当准确，我觉得
your limp's psychosomatic, quite correctly, I'm afraid.

333
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,550
这样应该可以继续下去了吧，你觉得呢？
That's enough to be going on with, don't you think?

334
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:43,200
名字是夏洛克·福尔摩斯
The name's Sherlock Holmes,

335
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:45,810
那地址是贝克街221B
and the address is 221 B Baker Street.

336
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:47,080
午安
Afternoon.

337
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,950
对，他总这样
Ya, he's always like that.

338
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,110
你好
Hello.

339
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:03,230
- 福尔摩斯先生  - 叫夏洛克就好
- Ah, Mr Holmes. - Sherlock, please.

340
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:06,470
这儿是主城区，肯定很贵吧
Well, this is a prime spot. Must be expensive.

341
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:09,470
哈德森太太，就是房东，给我特惠价
Mrs Hudson, the landlady, she's given me a special deal.

342
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,750
欠我个人情，几年前
Owes me a favour. A few years back,

343
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,890
她丈夫在弗罗里达被判死刑
her husband got himself sentenced to death in Florida.

344
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,550
我帮了一下
I was able to help out.

345
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:18,190
抱歉，你阻止了她丈夫受刑？
Sorry, you stopped her husband being executed?

346
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,790
不，我确保了行刑
Oh, no, I ensured it.

347
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:23,350
夏洛克
Sherlock!

348
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,950
哈德森太太  这位是约翰·华生医生
Mrs Hudson, DrJohn Watson.

349
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:26,950
- 你好 请进吧   - 谢谢
- Hello. Come in. - Thank you.

350
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:28,030
我们走吧
Shall we...?

351
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:55,670
可以弄得很好
Well, this could be very nice.

352
00:13:57,700 --> 00:13:58,990
的确很好
Very nice indeed.

353
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,430
是的
Yes.

354
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:03,830
是的，我也这么想，我的想法一样
Yes, I think so, my thoughts precisely.

355
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:06,830
- 所以我就直接搬进来了 - 只要清掉这些垃圾
-So I went straight ahead and moved in.-Soon as we get this rubbish cleaned up.

356
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:13,950
- 那这都是...  - 哦，显然我可以收拾下
-So this is all... -Well, obviously I can straighten things up

357
00:14:14,070 --> 00:14:15,050
稍微的
a bit.

358
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:18,030
- 那是颗骷髅  - 我的一个朋友
- That's a skull. - Friend of mine.

359
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:19,670
我说朋友...
When I say friend...

360
00:14:19,830 --> 00:14:22,310
你觉得如何，华生医生？
What do you think, then, Dr Watson?

361
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:26,790
楼上还有间卧室，如果你们需要两间卧室的话
There's another bedroom upstairs, if you'll be needing two bedrooms.

362
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:28,710
我们当然需要两间
Of course we'll be needing two.

363
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:31,140
哦，别担心，这里各种人都有
Oh, don't worry, there's all sorts round here.

364
00:14:31,170 --> 00:14:33,670
隔壁特纳太太家有一对结婚了的
Mrs Turner next door's got married ones.

365
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:40,310
夏洛克  看你弄这么乱
Oh...Sherlock! The mess you've made.

366
00:14:47,180 --> 00:14:48,900
昨晚我在网上搜了下你
I looked you up on the internet last night.

367
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:52,400
有什么有意思的吗？
Anything interesting?

368
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:55,300
找到了你的网站  "演绎学"
Found your website. The Science Of Deduction.

369
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:56,700
你怎么想？
What did you think?

370
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:01,590
你说你能通过领带识别一名软件工程师
You said you could identify a software designer by his tie

371
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,390
通过左手大拇指识别民航飞行员
and an airline pilot by his left thumb?

372
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:04,630
是的
Yes.

373
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:07,270
我还能通过你的脸和腿  看出你的军人职业
And I can read your military career in your face and your leg,

374
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:10,350
通过你的手机  知道你哥的饮酒习惯
and your brother's drinking habits in your mobile phone.

375
00:15:10,940 --> 00:15:11,950
怎么办到的？
How?

376
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:15,150
这些自杀案怎么样，夏洛克？
What about these suicides, then, Sherlock?

377
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,550
我觉得这正是你拿手的
I thought that'd be right up your street.

378
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:19,900
三起完全一样
Three exactly the same.

379
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:21,390
四起
Four.

380
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,890
有第四起了，而且这次有些不同
There's been a fourth. And there's something different this time.

381
00:15:26,110 --> 00:15:27,050
第四起？
A fourth?

382
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:32,510
- 哪里？  - 布里克斯顿的劳瑞斯顿花园
- Where? - Brixton, Lauriston Gardens.

383
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:35,350
这次有什么新情况？不然你不会来找我
What's new about this one? You wouldn't have come to me if there wasn't something differente.

384
00:15:35,430 --> 00:15:37,130
- 你知道他们从未有留言吧？  - 对
- You know how they never leave notes? - Yes.

385
00:15:37,230 --> 00:15:38,030
这次有
This one did.

386
00:15:38,830 --> 00:15:39,380
你来吗？
Will you come?

387
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:42,310
- 谁是法医？  - 安德森
- Who's on forensics? - Anderson.

388
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,590
他跟我合不来
He doesn't work well with me.

389
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,190
- 他又不会当你助手  - 我需要一个助手
- Well, he won't be your assistant. - I need an assistant.

390
00:15:47,350 --> 00:15:49,910
- 你来吗？  - 不坐警车，我就跟在后面
- Will you come? - Not in a police car, I'll be right behind.

391
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,710
谢谢
Thank you.

392
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:02,350
太棒了！耶！
Brilliant! Yes!

393
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,580
四起连环自杀案件  现在还有留言
Four serial suicides and now a note.

394
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,140
哦，过圣诞了
Oh, it's Christmas.

395
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:09,630
哈德森太太  我会晚归  可能需要点吃的
Mrs Hudson, I'll be late. Might need some food.

396
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:12,430
我是你房东，亲爱的，不是管家
I'm your landlady, dear, not your housekeeper.

397
00:16:12,470 --> 00:16:13,990
冷的食物就行，约翰
Something cold will do. John,

398
00:16:14,050 --> 00:16:16,030
来杯茶，跟在家里一样
have a cup of tea, make yourself at home.

399
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,790
不用等我
Don't wait up!

400
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:20,270
看看他，劲头十足...
Look at him, dashing about...

401
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:22,750
我丈夫以前也一样
My husband was just the same.

402
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:26,470
但你更属于坐得住的类型，我看得出来
But you're more the sitting-down type, I can tell.

403
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:29,510
我来帮你沏茶  你歇歇腿
I'll make you that cuppa, you rest your leg.

404
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:32,510
该死的腿！抱歉，我非常抱歉
Damn my leg! Sorry, I'm so sorry.

405
00:16:32,540 --> 00:16:35,030
只是有时这该死的东西…
It's just sometimes this bloody thing...

406
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,830
我理解，亲爱的，我臀部也是
I understand, dear, I've got a hip.

407
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,510
来杯茶就太好了，谢谢
Cup of tea'd be lovely. Thank you.

408
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,910
就这一次，亲爱的  我不是你管家
Just this once, dear, I'm not your housekeeper.

409
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:46,400
- 再来几片饼干，如果有的话   - 不是你管家哦
- Couple of biscuits too, if you've got 'em. - Not your housekeeper!

410
00:16:49,380 --> 00:16:50,870
你是个医生
You're a doctor.

411
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:53,590
实际上，你是一名军医
In fact, you're an Army doctor.

412
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,070
是的
Yes.

413
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,430
做得好吗？
Any good?

414
00:16:59,550 --> 00:17:00,560
非常好
Very good.

415
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:04,230
见过无数创伤，是吧，致命的伤
Seen a lot of injuries, then. Violent deaths.

416
00:17:04,320 --> 00:17:06,230
呃，是啊
Well, yes.

417
00:17:06,540 --> 00:17:07,830
有点困扰，我打赌？
Bit of trouble too, I bet?

418
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:12,150
当然，是的，这辈子看够了，太多了
Of course. Yes. Enough for a lifetime, far too much.

419
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:16,000
- 还想看更多吗  - 哦，老天，当然
- Want to see some more? - Oh, God, yes.

420
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,960
抱歉，哈德森太太，不喝茶了  要出去
Sorry, Mrs Hudson, I'll skip the tea. Off out.

421
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:24,000
你俩都去？
Both of you?

422
00:17:24,340 --> 00:17:26,330
不可能的自杀案件？四起？
Impossible suicides? Four of them?

423
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:29,230
没理由坐在家里，终于有好玩的了
No point sitting at home when there's finally something fun going on!

424
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:32,930
- 看看你，满心欢喜，这不得体  - 管他得不得体
- Look at you, all happy. It's not decent. - Who cares about decent?

425
00:17:32,950 --> 00:17:35,270
游戏，哈德森太太，开始了
The game, Mrs Hudson, is on!

426
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:42,430
出租车
Taxi!

427
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:20,660
好吧，你有一些问题…
OK, you've got questions...

428
00:18:20,670 --> 00:18:21,510
对，我们要去哪儿？
Yeah, where are we going?

429
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:25,000
犯罪现场，下一个？
Crime scene. Next?

430
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,270
- 你是谁？做什么的？  - 你觉得呢？
- Who are you? What do you do? - What do you think?

431
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:31,000
- 我本想说...私家侦探  - 但是...
- I'd say...private detective. - But...?

432
00:18:31,140 --> 00:18:32,830
但警察不会找私家侦探
But the police don't go to private detectives.

433
00:18:33,670 --> 00:18:35,350
我是个“咨询侦探”
I'm a consulting detective.

434
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:37,690
全世界独此一家，我发明的职业
Only one in the world. I invented the job.

435
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:38,710
那是什么意思？
What does that mean?

436
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:41,480
意思是警察束手无策时 这是常有的
It means when the police are out of their depth, which is always,

437
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,480
他们就咨询我
they consult me.

438
00:18:42,540 --> 00:18:44,730
警察不会咨询业余人员
The police don't consult amateurs.

439
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,310
我昨天第一次见到你时
When I met you for the first time yesterday,

440
00:18:49,320 --> 00:18:50,820
我说是阿富汗还是伊拉克
I said Afghanistan or Iraq.

441
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:52,420
- 你看起来很惊讶  - 对，你怎么知道的
- You looked surprised. - Yes, how did you know?

442
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:54,210
我不知道，我看到
I didn't know, I saw.

443
00:18:54,950 --> 00:18:57,090
你的发型，站立姿势说明是军人
Your haircut, the way you hold yourself says military.

444
00:18:57,110 --> 00:19:00,070
- 但你说的话...  - 跟我那会儿有点不一样了
- But your conversation... - Bit different from my day.

445
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:02,750
说明在巴茨医院受训过  所以显然是军医
...said trained at Barts - so Army doctor, obvious.

446
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,200
你的脸晒黑了
Your face is tanned...

447
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:07,220
但手腕以上却没晒黑
but no tan above the wrists.

448
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,220
说明你从国外回来  但不是日光浴
You've been abroad, but not sunbathing.

449
00:19:09,340 --> 00:19:10,650
你走路时跛得厉害
Your limp's really bad when you walk,

450
00:19:10,660 --> 00:19:13,330
站立时却没要一把椅子，好像你忘了这事
but you don't ask for a chair when you stand, like you've forgotten about it,

451
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:15,270
所以多少有一部分是心理问题
so it's at least partly psychosomatic.

452
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:18,330
那说明受伤的原始环境是外伤
That says the original circumstances of the injury were traumatic.

453
00:19:18,350 --> 00:19:19,900
是战斗负伤，战斗负伤
Wounded in action, then. Wounded in action,

454
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:23,210
晒黑  那就是阿富汗或伊拉克
suntan - Afghanistan or Iraq.

455
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:25,030
你说我在看心理咨询
You said I had a therapist.

456
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:28,150
你的跛脚是身心失调，当然要心理咨询
You've got a psychosomatic limp, of course you've got a therapist.

457
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:29,650
再说你的兄弟
Then there's your brother.

458
00:19:29,860 --> 00:19:32,820
你的手机，很贵，能收发邮件，放MP3
Your phone. It's expensive, e-mail enabled, MP3 player.

459
00:19:32,830 --> 00:19:35,310
你在找人合租，不会是自己买的，那么它是个礼物
You're looking for a flatshare. You wouldn't buy this - it's a gift then.

460
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,710
有刮痕  不止一两条  而是很多
Scratches. Not one, many over time -

461
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,710
肯定是跟钥匙硬币放在同一个口袋
it's been in the same pocket as keys and coins.

462
00:19:39,730 --> 00:19:41,750
你不会这样对自己的奢侈品
You wouldn't treat your one luxury item like this,

463
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,190
所以它以前有个主人
so it's had a previous owner.

464
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:44,910
下一个就简单了  你已经知道了
Next bit's easy. You know it already.

465
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:46,590
刻的字吗
The engraving?

466
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:49,480
海瑞·华生，明显是一个家庭成员给了你他的旧手机
Harry Watson. Clearly a family member who's given you his old phone.

467
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:51,670
不是你父亲，这是年轻人款式
Not your father, this is a young man's gadget.

468
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:54,710
可能是表兄弟，但你是战斗英雄，找不到地方住
Could be a cousin, but you're a war hero who can't find a place to live.

469
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:57,670
不太可能你有个大家庭，当然不是你亲近的人
Unlikely you've got an extended family, certainly not one you're close to.

470
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:58,730
那就是你兄弟
So brother it is.

471
00:19:58,740 --> 00:20:00,230
现在说克拉拉，谁是克拉拉？
Now, Clara, who's Clara?

472
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:02,410
 “三个吻”说明两人是爱情关系
Three kisses says it's a romantic attachment.

473
00:20:02,420 --> 00:20:04,430
手机昂贵，说明是妻子，不是女友
The expense of the phone says wife, not girlfriend.

474
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,630
肯定是最近才送的，这一款才发布六个月
Must have given it to him recently, the model's only six months old.

475
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:10,120
那就是婚姻出了问题  才用了六个月就送人
Marriage in trouble, then - six months on he's given it away.

476
00:20:10,130 --> 00:20:12,230
如果是她离开他，他就会留着，人之常情，多愁善感
If she'd left him, he would have kept it. Peaple do, sentiment.

477
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:14,390
不，他想甩掉它，是他离开了她
No, he wanted rid of it. He left her.

478
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:16,880
他把手机给了你，那说明他想跟你保持联系
He gave the phone to you, so he wants you to stay in touch.

479
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:18,800
你在找便宜住处
You're looking for cheap accommodation,

480
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,400
却不去向自己兄弟求助
but not going to your brother for help.

481
00:20:20,850 --> 00:20:22,220
这说明你跟他之间有问题
That says you've got problems with him.

482
00:20:22,230 --> 00:20:25,200
也许是你喜欢他妻子，也许是你讨厌他喝酒
Maybe you liked his wife or maybe you don't like his drinking.

483
00:20:25,210 --> 00:20:28,910
你怎么可能知道喝酒的事？
How can you possibly know about the drinking?

484
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:30,790
瞎猜的，不过猜得很好
Shot in the dark. Good one, though.

485
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:33,160
电源插口  周围有细小的磨损痕迹
Power connection - tiny little scuff marks round the edge.

486
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:35,790
每晚他插上充电  但手总是在抖
Every night he goes to plug it in to charge, but his hands are shaking.

487
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,630
你绝不会在清醒的人手机上看到这种痕迹
You never see those marks on a sober man's phone,

488
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:40,270
醉鬼的手机上则绝不会没有，所以，瞧，你说得对
never see a drunk's without them. There you go, you were right.

489
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,240
我说得对？我说对了什么？
I was right? Right about what?

490
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:44,390
警察不会请教业余人员
The police don't consult amateurs.

491
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:49,870
这真是…太了不起了
That...was amazing.

492
00:20:53,540 --> 00:20:54,790
- 你这么觉得吗？  - 当然是了
- Do you think so? - Of course it was.

493
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,470
这是非凡的，非同凡响
It was extraordinary, quite extraordinary.

494
00:20:57,480 --> 00:21:00,070
- 别人一般不这么说  - 别人一般说什么？
- That's not what people normally say. - What do people normally say?

495
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,590
滚开
Piss off!

496
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,110
我有没有弄错什么？
Did I get anything wrong?

497
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:18,500
海瑞和我相处不来，从没好过
Harry and me don't get on, never have.

498
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:22,370
克拉拉和海瑞分手了，三个月前
Clara and Harry split up three months ago

499
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,900
他们正在办离婚
and they're getting a divorce.

500
00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:26,110
而且海瑞是个酒徒
And Harry is a drinker.

501
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,410
那就是全中，我倒没期望事事都对
Spot on, then. I didn't expect to be right about everything.

502
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:30,150
海瑞是海莉特的昵称
Harry's short for Harriet.

503
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,550
海瑞是你姐姐
Harry's your sister.

504
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,920
- 我来这到底该干嘛来着？  - 姐姐
- What exactly am I supposed to be doing here? - Sister!

505
00:21:34,930 --> 00:21:38,550
- 不，说真的，我来干嘛？  - 总是有点错
- No, seriously, what am I doing here? - There's always something.

506
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:39,730
你好  怪胎
Hello, freak!

507
00:21:40,140 --> 00:21:42,230
我来找雷斯垂德探长
I'm here to see Detective Inspector Lestrade.

508
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:43,210
为什么
Why?

509
00:21:43,820 --> 00:21:45,010
我是受邀前来
I was invited.

510
00:21:45,350 --> 00:21:47,170
- 为什么？  - 我想他要我来看看
- Why? - I think he wants me to take a look.

511
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:50,060
- 你知道我的想法，对吧  - 一向知道，萨莉
- You know what I think, don't you? - Always, Sally.

512
00:21:50,660 --> 00:21:53,110
我甚至知道你昨晚没回家
I even know you didn't make it home last night.

513
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:56,110
- 我没…这位是谁？  - 我同事  华生医生
- Er...who's this? - Colleague of mine, Dr Watson.

514
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:58,320
华生医生  这位是萨莉·多诺万警佐
Dr Watson, Sergeant Sally Donovan.

515
00:21:58,650 --> 00:21:59,750
老朋友
Old friend.

516
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:03,230
一个同事？你怎么会有同事？
A colleague? How do you get a colleague?

517
00:22:03,380 --> 00:22:04,840
怎么？他跟踪你回家了？
What? Did he follow you home?

518
00:22:04,860 --> 00:22:07,390
- 我在这里等着是不是更好  - 不
- Would it be better if I just waited...? - No.

519
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,320
怪胎来了 我带他进去
Freak's here. Bringing him in.

520
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:22,320
哦，安德森，又见面了
Ah, Anderson. Here we are again.

521
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:26,250
这是犯罪现场，我不想它被污染，说清楚了吗
It's a crime scene. I don't want it contaminated. Are we clear on that?

522
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,850
清楚得很
Quite clear.

523
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:30,050
你妻子很久不回家了吧？
And is your wife away for long?

524
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:32,670
别装得像你自己推理出来的，有人告诉你的吧
Oh, don't pretend you worked that out. Somebody told you that.

525
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:34,110
你的体香剂告诉我的
Your deodorant told me that.

526
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,730
- 我的体香剂？  - 是男用的
- My deodorant? - It's for men.

527
00:22:37,070 --> 00:22:39,080
当然是男用的，就是我在用啊
Well, of course it's for men - I'm wearing it.

528
00:22:39,110 --> 00:22:40,230
多诺万警佐也用了
So's Sergeant Donovan.

529
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:44,450
哦，它刚挥发掉了，我能进去了吗
Ooh...I think it just vaporised. May I go in?

530
00:22:44,460 --> 00:22:47,500
- 听着，不管你在暗示什么  - 我什么都没暗示
- Now, look, whatever you're trying to imply... - I'm not implying anything.

531
00:22:47,510 --> 00:22:49,800
我肯定萨莉只是顺道找你聊个小天
I'm sure Sally came round for a nice little chat

532
00:22:49,810 --> 00:22:51,910
再碰巧过了个夜
and just happened to stay over.

533
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:57,000
我猜她还替你擦了地板，从她膝盖的状况来看
And I assume she scrubbed your floors, going by the state of her knees.

534
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:08,430
你得穿一件这衣服
You'll need to wear one of these.

535
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:09,400
这是哪位？
Who's this?

536
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:11,430
他跟我一起的
He's with me.

537
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:14,150
- 但他究竟是谁？  - 我说了跟我一起的
- But who is he? - I said he's with me.

538
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,010
你不穿一件吗？
Aren't you going to put one on?

539
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:24,150
- 我们去哪？  - 楼上
- So where are we? - Upstairs.

540
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,630
我可以给你两分钟
I can give you two minutes.

541
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:35,650
可能要更久
May need longer.

542
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,670
她名叫詹妮弗·威尔逊，根据她的信用卡
Her name's Jennifer Wilson, according to her credit cards.

543
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:41,350
我们正根据信用卡查她的联系方式
We're running them now for contact details.

544
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:43,110
时间还没过太久
Hasn't been here long.

545
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,790
几个孩子发现的
Some kids found her.

546
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:19,430
闭嘴
Shut up.

547
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:22,800
- 我什么也没说  - 你在思考，很吵
- I didn't say anything. - You were thinking. It's annoying.

548
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,730
有发现吗？
Got anything?

549
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,070
不太多
Not much.

550
00:25:39,110 --> 00:25:40,150
她是德国人
She's German.

551
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:44,950
Rache 是德语的复仇  她可能想告诉我们...
Rache. It's German for revenge. She could be trying to tell us...

552
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,790
好了，感谢参与
Yes, thank you for your input.

553
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:50,380
- 她是德国人吗？  - 当然不是  不过倒是外地来的
- So she's German? - Of course she's not. She's from out of town, though.

554
00:25:50,380 --> 00:25:51,930
打算在回加迪夫的家之前
Intended to stay in London for one night

555
00:25:52,140 --> 00:25:55,120
在伦敦小住一夜，很明显
before returning home to Cardiff - so far, so obvious.

556
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:57,030
- 什么，很明显？  - 那这条信息呢？
- Sorry, obvious? - What about the message, though?

557
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:58,470
华生医生，你怎么看？
Dr Watson, what do you think?

558
00:25:59,100 --> 00:26:00,840
- 那条信息吗？  - 尸体，你是医务人员
- Of the message? - Of the body. You're a medical man.

559
00:26:00,870 --> 00:26:02,570
我们外面有一队人呢
We have a whole team outside.

560
00:26:02,650 --> 00:26:03,520
他们不和我一起工作
They won't work with me.

561
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:05,300
我坏了所有规矩放你进来
I'm breaking every rule letting you in here...

562
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:07,500
是的，因为你需要我
Yes, because you need me.

563
00:26:09,030 --> 00:26:10,270
是的，是这样
Yes, I do.

564
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:12,550
老天帮帮我
God help me.

565
00:26:12,830 --> 00:26:14,350
华生医生
Dr Watson!

566
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:18,110
哦，按他说的做  请便
Oh, do as he says. Help yourself.

567
00:26:20,850 --> 00:26:23,990
安德森，让大家在外面多等几分钟
Anderson, keep everyone out for a couple of minutes...

568
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:27,330
- 好吧  - 要我在这儿做什么
- Well? - What am I doing here?

569
00:26:27,420 --> 00:26:28,640
帮我理清思路
Helping me make a point.

570
00:26:28,650 --> 00:26:29,930
我本是帮你分担房租的
I'm supposed to help you pay the rent.

571
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:31,210
这更好玩
This is more fun.

572
00:26:31,220 --> 00:26:33,270
好玩？一个女人横死在这里
Fun? There's a woman lying dead.

573
00:26:33,940 --> 00:26:36,910
完美的分析  不过我希望你再深入些
Perfectly sound analysis, but I was hoping you'd go deeper.

574
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:58,490
对...窒息...可能
Yeah... Asphyxiation...probably.

575
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:00,670
昏倒，被她自己的呕吐物噎住
Passed out, choked on her own vomit.

576
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,500
她身上闻不出酒精
Can't smell any alcohol on her.

577
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:04,470
可以是癫痫发作  可能是药物
It could have been a seizure. Possibly drugs.

578
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:06,550
你知道那是什么  你读过报纸
You know what it was, you've read the papers.

579
00:27:07,100 --> 00:27:09,060
对，她是自杀者之一，第四个...
Well, she's one of the suicides. The fourth...?

580
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:10,340
夏洛克  我说过你2分钟
Sherlock, two minutes, I said.

581
00:27:10,340 --> 00:27:11,750
我需要你的发现
I need anything you've got.

582
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:13,400
死者年龄三十大几
Victim is in her late 30s.

583
00:27:13,430 --> 00:27:15,110
职业女性  从她的衣着来看
Professional person, going by her clothes.

584
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:18,410
我猜是媒体业，根据那触目惊心的粉红色
I'm guessing something in the media, going by the frankly alarming shade of pink.

585
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:19,820
今天刚从加迪夫过来
Travelled from Cardiff today

586
00:27:19,830 --> 00:27:22,850
打算在伦敦住一晚，看她手提箱的大小就知道了
intending to stay in London for one night from the size of her suitcase.

587
00:27:22,860 --> 00:27:24,010
- 手提箱？  - 对  手提箱
- Suitcase? - Suitcase, yes.

588
00:27:24,030 --> 00:27:26,760
她结婚起码10年  但不幸福
She's been married at least ten years, but not happily.

589
00:27:26,770 --> 00:27:29,600
她有一串情人  但没一个知道她结婚了
She's had a string of lovers, but none of them knew she was married.

590
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,630
老天啊  这要都是你编出来...
Oh, for God's sake, if you're just making this up...

591
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:34,190
她的婚戒  起码已经有10年了
Her wedding ring. Ten years old at least.

592
00:27:34,340 --> 00:27:36,210
她别的首饰都做过定期保养
The rest of herjewellery has been regularly cleaned,

593
00:27:36,230 --> 00:27:38,900
而婚戒却没有  她的婚姻状况就是如此
but not her wedding ring. State of her marriage right there.

594
00:27:38,910 --> 00:27:40,730
戒指的里圈要比外圈光亮许多
The inside is shinier than the outside,

595
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:41,930
说明经常拿下来
that means it's regularly removed.

596
00:27:41,950 --> 00:27:44,150
戒指只有在她取下来时才会被磨亮
The only polishing it gets is when she works it off her finger.

597
00:27:44,550 --> 00:27:45,750
不是为了工作，看看她的指甲
It's not for work, look at her nails.

598
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:46,940
她不是做手工活的
She doesn't work with her hands,

599
00:27:46,950 --> 00:27:49,530
那她是为了什么或是谁取下戒指呢
so what or who does she remove her rings for?

600
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:50,630
显然不是一个情人
Clearly not one lover

601
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,990
她绝不能这么长时间编造单身身份
she'd never sustain the fiction of being single for that long,

602
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:55,870
- 因此肯定不止一个  简单  - 厉害
- so more likely a string of them. Simple. - That's brilliant.

603
00:27:55,960 --> 00:27:57,510
- 抱歉  - 加迪夫呢？
- Sorry. - Cardiff?

604
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:59,200
很明显，不是吗
It's obvious, isn't it?

605
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:00,830
对我不明显
It's not obvious to me.

606
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:05,200
神啊，你那可笑的小脑袋是啥样？一定蛮无聊的
Dear God, what is it like in your funny little brains? It must be so boring.

607
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:06,150
她的外套
Her coat

608
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:08,790
有点潮湿  几小时前她一定淋了场大雨
it's slightly damp, she's been in heavy rain in the last few hours -

609
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,570
当时伦敦任何地方都没下雨
no rain anywhere in London in that time.

610
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:12,380
外套领子下面也是湿的
Under her coat collar is damp too.

611
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:14,150
她曾把领子立起来挡风
She's turned it up against the wind.

612
00:28:14,340 --> 00:28:16,990
她左边口袋里有把伞  但是干的  没用过
She's got an umbrella in her left pocket, but it's dry and unused.

613
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:19,410
不单有风 是大风  大到无法撑伞
Not just wind, strong wind - too strong to use her umbrella.

614
00:28:19,420 --> 00:28:21,980
我们从她的手提箱可知，她准备过夜
We know from her suitcase that she was intending to stay overnight

615
00:28:21,990 --> 00:28:23,150
所以她一定来自远方
so she must come distance

616
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,920
但她不可能已外出超过两三个小时
but she can't have travelled more than two or three hours,

617
00:28:24,930 --> 00:28:26,230
因为她的外套还没干
because her coat still hasn't dried.

618
00:28:26,270 --> 00:28:30,810
所以 在其旅行时间半径内 什么地方曾有过大风大雨？
So, where has there been heavy rain and strong wind within the radius of that travel time?

619
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:31,990
加迪夫
Cardiff.

620
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:34,470
- 太神奇了  - 你知道自己说出声来了吗
- That's fantastic. - Do you know you do that out loud?

621
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:36,910
- 抱歉 我会闭嘴的  - 不  没关系
- Sorry, I'll shut up. - No, it's...fine.

622
00:28:37,300 --> 00:28:38,640
你为什么总提到手提箱？
Why do you keep saying suitcase?

623
00:28:38,650 --> 00:28:39,950
对，它在哪里？
Yes, where is it?

624
00:28:40,450 --> 00:28:42,650
她肯定带了手机或是电子本
She must have had a phone or an organiser.

625
00:28:42,700 --> 00:28:43,780
查出瑞琪儿是何人
Find out who Rachel is.

626
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:45,110
她写的是瑞琪儿？
She was writing Rachel?

627
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:47,390
不，她写的是复仇的德语
No, she was leaving an angry note in German!

628
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:49,670
当然写的是瑞琪儿 不可能是别的字
Of course she was writing Rachel, no other word it can be.

629
00:28:49,760 --> 00:28:52,110
问题是她为何要等到临死前才写这个
But the question is why did she wait until she was dying to write it?

630
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:53,650
你怎么知道她有个手提箱？
How do you know she had a suitcase?

631
00:28:53,970 --> 00:28:54,720
看看右腿
Look at the right leg.

632
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:57,200
右脚踝和小腿上有小泥点，而左腿上没有
Tiny splash marks on her right heel and calf not present on the left.

633
00:28:57,220 --> 00:28:59,390
她用右手拖着个轮式手提箱在后面
She was dragging a wheeled suitcase behind her with her right hand.

634
00:28:59,750 --> 00:29:01,330
那些泥点没有飞到别处
Don't get that splash pattern any other way.

635
00:29:01,500 --> 00:29:03,350
是短小的箱子，根据泥点分布
Smallish case, going by the spread.

636
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,430
那种尺寸的箱子，这样穿着的女人
Case that size, woman this clothes-conscious -

637
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,730
只可能是一只过夜旅行箱
could only be an overnight bag

638
00:29:06,740 --> 00:29:08,020
所以我们知道她打算过一夜
so we know she was staying one night.

639
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:09,590
它在哪里？你们检查过了吗
Where is it? What have you done with it?

640
00:29:09,780 --> 00:29:11,470
没有箱子
There wasn't a case.

641
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:15,210
再说一次
Say that again.

642
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,520
没有箱子，这里根本就没有什么手提箱
There wasn't a case. There was never any suitcase.

643
00:29:17,620 --> 00:29:19,980
手提箱，有谁见过一个手提箱？
Suitcase! Did anyone find a suitcase?

644
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,830
这房子里有手提箱吗
Was there a suitcase in this house?

645
00:29:21,870 --> 00:29:23,430
夏洛克，这里没有箱子
Sherlock, there was no case!

646
00:29:23,730 --> 00:29:24,980
但他们自己服毒
But they take the poison themselves,

647
00:29:25,030 --> 00:29:26,340
他们自己选择吞下药丸
they choose swallow the pills themselves.

648
00:29:26,360 --> 00:29:28,630
迹象明显，就算是你的手下也不可能错过
There are clear signs, even you lot couldn't miss them.

649
00:29:28,650 --> 00:29:30,130
好吧  谢谢  还有呢
Right, thanks. And...?

650
00:29:30,620 --> 00:29:32,810
是谋杀，全都是，我还没搞清
It's murder, all of them. I don't know how.

651
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:35,530
但绝不是自杀，是他杀，连环杀人案
But they're not suicides, they're killings, they're serial killings.

652
00:29:35,550 --> 00:29:37,230
一个连环杀人犯，我爱死了
We've got a serial killer. Love those.

653
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:38,750
总能让人有各种期待
There's always something to look forward to.

654
00:29:39,100 --> 00:29:40,100
你为什么这么说？
Why are you saying that?

655
00:29:40,220 --> 00:29:42,300
她的箱子，拜托，她的箱子在哪里？
Her case! Come on, where is her case?

656
00:29:42,310 --> 00:29:43,650
是她吃了吗？
Did she eat it?

657
00:29:43,660 --> 00:29:46,430
另有别人来过这里，并拿走了她的箱子
Someone else was here and they took her case.

658
00:29:46,950 --> 00:29:48,410
所以凶手必是驱车至此
So the killer must have driven here.

659
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:49,750
忘了箱子在车上
Forgot the case was in the car.

660
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:52,050
她也可能先入住酒店，把箱子留在那里
She could have checked into a hotel, left it there.

661
00:29:52,130 --> 00:29:54,450
不，她从没到过酒店，看看她的头发
No, she never got to the hotel. Look at her hair.

662
00:29:54,700 --> 00:29:56,520
她的颜色搭配，唇彩和鞋子
She colour-coordinates her lipstick and shoes.

663
00:29:56,540 --> 00:29:59,790
她绝不会那样离开酒店，她的头发还…
She'd never have left any hotel with her hair still looking...

664
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,400
夏洛克，是什么，是什么？
Sherlock? What is it, what?

665
00:30:05,450 --> 00:30:07,000
连环杀人犯总是很难搞
Serial killers, always hard.

666
00:30:07,700 --> 00:30:09,070
你得等他们犯一个错误
You have to wait for them to make a mistake.

667
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:09,990
我们不能光等着
We can't just wait!

668
00:30:10,030 --> 00:30:11,810
等待已经结束了，看看她，仔细看
Oh, we're done waiting. Look at her, really look!

669
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:14,650
休斯顿，我们有错误了  快去加迪夫
Houston, we have a mistake. Get on to Cardiff.

670
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:16,930
找到詹妮弗·威尔逊的家人和朋友在哪
Find out who Jennifer Wilson's family and friends were.

671
00:30:16,940 --> 00:30:17,780
找到瑞琪儿
Find Rachel!

672
00:30:17,820 --> 00:30:19,590
当然，好  但是什么错误？
Of course, yeah - but what mistake?!

673
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:22,550
粉色
Pink!

674
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:26,210
我们开工
Let's get on with it...

675
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,850
- 他走了  - 夏洛克·福尔摩斯吗？
- He's gone. - Who, Sherlock Holmes?

676
00:31:05,860 --> 00:31:07,870
对，他刚走，他总这样
Yeah, he just took off. He does that.

677
00:31:08,100 --> 00:31:10,070
- 他还会回来吗？  - 看来不会
- Is he coming back? - Didn't look like it.

678
00:31:11,230 --> 00:31:12,320
好吧
Right.

679
00:31:14,100 --> 00:31:15,270
好吧
Right...

680
00:31:17,350 --> 00:31:19,590
好，打扰了，我在哪里？
Yes. Sorry, where am I?

681
00:31:20,350 --> 00:31:21,230
布里克斯顿
Brixton.

682
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:24,210
我…你知道我能在哪儿打到车吗
I...Do you know where I could get a cab?

683
00:31:24,420 --> 00:31:25,610
只是…
It's just, er...

684
00:31:26,900 --> 00:31:29,670
那个…我的腿
well... my leg.

685
00:31:32,870 --> 00:31:34,450
试试主路上
try the main road.

686
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:35,790
谢谢
Thanks.

687
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:38,310
可你不是他的朋友
But you're not his friend.

688
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:40,390
他没有朋友
He doesn't have friends.

689
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,470
所以你是谁呢？
So who are you?

690
00:31:43,730 --> 00:31:46,530
我…我谁也不是，我刚认识他
I'm...I'm nobody. I just met him.

691
00:31:46,540 --> 00:31:48,630
好吧，一点忠告，离那人远点
OK, bit of advice, then. Stay away from that guy.

692
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,000
为什么？
Why?

693
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:53,800
你知道他为什么来这里吗？
You know why he's here?

694
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:57,500
他没有报酬什么的
He's not paid or anything.

695
00:31:57,950 --> 00:32:00,110
他喜欢这个，他乐在其中
He likes it. He gets off on it.

696
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:04,350
犯罪越古怪，他越享受，而且知道吗？
The weirder the crime, the more he gets off. And you know what...?

697
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:07,750
总有一天，揭露犯罪不再能满足他
One day just showing up won't be enough.

698
00:32:07,930 --> 00:32:09,270
总有一天，我们会站在一具尸体边
One day we'll be standing round a body,

699
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:11,190
而夏洛克·福尔摩斯便是抛尸之人
and Sherlock Holmes'll be the one that put it there.

700
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:14,030
- 他为什么会这么做？  - 因为他就是个疯子
- Why would he do that? - Because he's a psychopath.

701
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:15,850
疯子容易无聊
Psychopaths get bored.

702
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:18,590
- 多诺万  - 来了
- Donovan! - Coming.

703
00:32:22,530 --> 00:32:25,070
离夏洛克·福尔摩斯远点
Stay away from Sherlock Holmes.

704
00:32:55,300 --> 00:32:57,630
出租车 出租车
Taxi! Taxi...

705
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:34,230
喂
Hello?

706
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:37,980
有个监控摄像头在你左边大楼上
There is a security camera on the building to your left.

707
00:33:38,050 --> 00:33:39,310
你看到了吗
Do you see it?

708
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:44,400
你是谁？
Who's this?

709
00:33:45,950 --> 00:33:47,030
谁在说话？
Who's speaking?

710
00:33:47,540 --> 00:33:50,030
你看到那个摄像头了吗，华生医生？
Do you see the camera, Dr Watson?

711
00:33:51,650 --> 00:33:53,500
- 对，我看到了  - 看好
- Yeah, I see it. - Watch...

712
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:01,230
还有一个摄像头在你对面的房子上
There is another camera on the building opposite you.

713
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:02,230
看到了吗
Do you see it?

714
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:09,510
最后，在你右边的楼顶上
And finally, at the top of the building on your right.

715
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:18,030
你怎么做到的？
How are you doing this?

716
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:21,120
上车，华生医生
Get into the car, Dr Watson.

717
00:34:21,380 --> 00:34:23,390
我不想发什么威胁
I would make some sort of threat,

718
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:26,790
但我肯定你相当清楚自己的处境
but I'm sure your situation is quite clear to you.

719
00:34:43,240 --> 00:34:45,830
- 你好  - 嗨
- Hello. - Hi.

720
00:34:51,100 --> 00:34:52,500
你叫什么名字？
What's your name, then?

721
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,790
哦…安茜娅
Er...Anthea.

722
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:57,630
这是你的真名吗？
Is that your real name?

723
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:58,630
不是
No.

724
00:35:02,950 --> 00:35:04,000
我叫约翰
I'm John.

725
00:35:04,500 --> 00:35:05,910
对，我知道
Yes. I know.

726
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:12,310
问这个有意义吗…我要去哪里？
Any point in asking...where I'm going?

727
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:17,000
完全没有
None at all...

728
00:35:17,450 --> 00:35:18,470
约翰
John.

729
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:21,190
好吧
Ok.

730
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:41,990
请坐，约翰
Have a seat, John.

731
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:48,390
你知道，我有手机
You know, I've got a phone.

732
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:52,350
我是说，你那些搞得很聪明
I mean, very clever and all that,

733
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:54,430
但是
but, er...

734
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:56,190
你可以直接打给我
you could just phone me.

735
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:58,670
打我手机
On my phone.

736
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:04,070
人要避开夏洛克·福尔摩斯的注意
When one is avoiding the attention of Sherlock Holmes,

737
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:06,450
就得谨慎些，所以挑了这地方
one learns to be discreet, hence this place.

738
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:09,580
你的腿一定很疼，坐吧
Your leg must be hurting you. Sit down.

739
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:11,110
我不想坐下
I don't want to sit down.

740
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:14,310
你看起来不太害怕
You don't seem very afraid.

741
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:15,750
你看起来不太吓人
You don't seem very frightening.

742
00:36:17,110 --> 00:36:18,390
是啊
Yes...

743
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:21,310
军人的勇敢
The bravery of the soldier.

744
00:36:21,750 --> 00:36:25,380
“勇敢”其实是“愚蠢”一词的仁慈说法，你不觉得吗
Bravery is by far the kindest word for stupidity, don't you think?

745
00:36:25,410 --> 00:36:28,010
你跟夏洛克·福尔摩斯是何关系？
What is your connection to Sherlock Holmes?

746
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:32,400
没有，我几乎不认识他，我跟他结识是在…
I don't have one. I barely know him. I met him...

