768
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,950
如果你真的搬入…
If you do move into, um...

769
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:38,870
贝克街221B
...22 1 B Baker Street,

770
00:37:39,100 --> 00:37:43,900
我将乐意定期给你提供一笔可观的费用，用以…
I'd be happy to pay you a meaningful sum of money on a regular basis

771
00:37:44,110 --> 00:37:45,110
替你分忧
to ease your way.

772
00:37:45,700 --> 00:37:46,600
为何？
Why?

773
00:37:46,900 --> 00:37:48,050
因为你不是有钱人
Because you're not a wealthy man.

774
00:37:48,080 --> 00:37:49,710
以此交换什么？
In exchange for what?

775
00:37:50,520 --> 00:37:52,000
情报
Information.

776
00:37:52,450 --> 00:37:56,100
无非分请求  不会让你感到…为难
Nothing indiscreet. Nothing you'd feel...uncomfortable with.

777
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:57,730
只需告诉我他在干什么
Just tell me what he's up to.

778
00:37:57,740 --> 00:37:58,470
为什么
Why?

779
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:02,910
我担心他，时不时地
I worry about him. Constantly.

780
00:38:03,750 --> 00:38:04,510
你真好
That's nice of you.

781
00:38:05,100 --> 00:38:09,260
不过出于各种理由，我宁愿我的关心不被提起
But I would prefer for various reasons that my concern go unmentioned.

782
00:38:09,270 --> 00:38:13,230
我们的关系你也许可以称之为…艰难
We have what you might call a... difficult relationship.

783
00:38:19,860 --> 00:38:22,270
- 不  - 可我还没提具体数字呢
- No. - But I haven't mentioned a figure.

784
00:38:22,410 --> 00:38:23,320
不必费心了
Don't bother.

785
00:38:23,750 --> 00:38:25,900
你非常忠诚，非常果断
You're very loyal very quickly.

786
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:28,710
不，我不是，我只是没兴趣
No, I'm not, I'm just not interested.

787
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:35,590
“信任危机” ，这里写着
"Trust issues", it says here.

788
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:40,600
那是什么？
What's that?

789
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:44,510
可不可以说 你已决定在所有人中信任夏洛克·福尔摩斯了？
Could it be that you've decided to trust Sherlock Holmes of all people?

790
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:45,660
谁说我信任他了？
Who says I trust him?

791
00:38:45,670 --> 00:38:47,550
你不像善交朋友的人
You don't seem the kind to make friends easily.

792
00:38:47,570 --> 00:38:48,710
咱们说完了吗
Are we done?

793
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:51,270
你说呢
You tell me.

794
00:38:58,440 --> 00:39:01,530
我想有人已警告过你远离他
I imagine people have already warned you to stay away from him,

795
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:04,710
不过我能从你的左手看出 你不会那么做
but I can see from your left hand that's not going to happen.

796
00:39:07,950 --> 00:39:10,310
- 我的什么？  - 给我看看
- My what? - Show me.

797
00:39:21,420 --> 00:39:22,330
不要…
Don't...

798
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:32,510
- 不一般  - 什么东西？
- Remarkable. - What is?

799
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:35,040
多数人在这城里东奔西撞
Most people blunder round this city

800
00:39:35,050 --> 00:39:39,010
他们所见只有街道、商铺和汽车
and all they see are streets and shops and cars.

801
00:39:39,750 --> 00:39:42,570
你和夏洛克·福尔摩斯一起行走时，你看到了战场
When you walk with Sherlock Holmes, you see the battlefield.

802
00:39:42,850 --> 00:39:44,690
你已经看到了，对吗？
You've seen it already, haven't you?

803
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,350
我的手怎么了？
What's wrong with my hand?

804
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:50,000
你的左手有间歇性颤抖
You have an intermittent tremor in your left hand.

805
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:53,470
你的理疗师认为那是创后应激障碍
Your therapist thinks it's post-traumatic stress disorder.

806
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:56,450
她认为你被军役生涯的记忆所纠缠
She thinks you're haunted by memories of your military service.

807
00:39:56,470 --> 00:39:57,990
你到底是谁？
Who the hell are you?

808
00:39:59,350 --> 00:40:00,550
这你怎么能知道？
How do you know that?

809
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:03,400
辞了她，她完全搞错了
Fire her. She's got it the wrong way round.

810
00:40:03,750 --> 00:40:07,000
你现在就处于压力下，而你的手完全稳定
You're under stress right now, and your hand is perfectly steady.

811
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:11,590
你不是受战争困扰，华生医生
You're not haunted by the war, Dr Watson...

812
00:40:13,050 --> 00:40:14,170
你想念它
You miss it.

813
00:40:16,950 --> 00:40:18,550
欢迎回来
Welcome back.

814
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:27,470
是时候选一边了，华生医生
Time to choose a side, Dr Watson.

815
00:40:37,130 --> 00:40:39,270
我来送你回家
I'm to take you home.

816
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:50,110
地址？
Address?

817
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:52,230
贝克街
Er, Baker Street.

818
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:55,030
贝克街221B
22 1 B Baker Street.

819
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:58,400
不过我得先去个地方
But I need to stop off somewhere first.

820
00:41:25,850 --> 00:41:27,030
听着，你的老板
Listen, your boss.

821
00:41:27,040 --> 00:41:29,600
有没有可能你不告诉他这是我来的地方？
Any chance you could not tell him this is where I went?

822
00:41:30,250 --> 00:41:32,510
- 可以  - 你已经告诉他了，对吧
- Sure. - You've told him already, haven't you?

823
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:34,070
对
Yeah.

824
00:41:39,550 --> 00:41:41,510
你有没有什么空闲时间？
do you ever get any free time?

825
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:43,870
有，很多
Oh, yeah. Lots.

826
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:51,630
- 拜  - 好
- Bye. - OK.

827
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:20,370
你在干什么？
What are you doing?

828
00:42:21,530 --> 00:42:22,620
尼古丁贴片
Nicotine patch.

829
00:42:23,810 --> 00:42:25,430
帮助我思考
Helps me think.

830
00:42:25,720 --> 00:42:29,330
这年头在伦敦 不可能维持吸烟的习惯
Impossible to sustain a smoking habit in London these days.

831
00:42:29,500 --> 00:42:31,050
对脑力劳动是坏消息
Bad news for brain work.

832
00:42:31,100 --> 00:42:32,220
对呼吸是好消息
It's good news for breathing.

833
00:42:32,220 --> 00:42:34,030
呼吸，呼吸太无聊
Oh, breathing! Breathing's boring.

834
00:42:34,040 --> 00:42:35,830
那是…三片吗？
Is that...three patches?

835
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:37,810
这是三片难度的问题
It's a three-patch problem.

836
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:43,030
嗯
Well...?

837
00:42:45,650 --> 00:42:48,030
你要我回来  我想是要紧事
You asked me to come, I'm assuming it's important.

838
00:42:49,140 --> 00:42:51,210
对  当然  我能借用你的手机吗？
Oh, yeah, of course. Can I borrow your phone?

839
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:53,310
我的手机？
My phone?

840
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:55,730
我的号码有可能被认出来
There's always a chance that my number will be recognised.

841
00:42:55,730 --> 00:42:56,690
网站上有
It's on the website.

842
00:42:56,700 --> 00:42:57,790
哈德森太太有手机
Mrs Hudson's got a phone.

843
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:58,500
对，她在楼下
Yeah, she's downstairs.

844
00:42:58,510 --> 00:42:59,820
我试过喊了，但她没听见
I tried shouting, but she didn't hear.

845
00:42:59,830 --> 00:43:01,080
我当时在伦敦另一头
I was the other side of London...

846
00:43:01,090 --> 00:43:01,790
这不急
There was no hurry.

847
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:07,350
给...
Here...

848
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:14,190
那么，那个箱子怎么了
So what's this about the case?

849
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:16,460
- 她的箱子  - 她的箱子？
- Her case... - Her case?

850
00:43:16,470 --> 00:43:18,630
她的手提箱，对，很明显
Her suitcase, yes, obviously.

851
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:22,070
凶手拿走她的手提箱  第一个大错
The murderer took her suitcase, first big mistake.

852
00:43:22,160 --> 00:43:23,750
好吧，他拿了她的箱子，所以？
OK, he took her case. So?

853
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:26,600
这没用，没别的办法了，我们得冒个险
It's no use, there's no other way. We'll have to risk it.

854
00:43:27,700 --> 00:43:30,510
我书桌上有个手机号  我要你发个短信
On my desk there's a number. I want you to send a text.

855
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:35,130
你叫我回来…就发个短信？
You've brought me here... to send a text.

856
00:43:35,140 --> 00:43:37,130
短信，对，号码在我桌上
Text, yes. The number on my desk.

857
00:43:49,300 --> 00:43:51,850
- 怎么了？  - 刚才见了你一位朋友
- What's wrong? - Just met a friend of yours.

858
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:53,860
- 一个朋友？  - 一个敌人
- A friend? - An enemy.

859
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:55,270
哦，哪个？
Oh. Which one?

860
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:59,220
你的死敌，他说的
Well, your arch-enemy, according to him.

861
00:43:59,230 --> 00:44:00,650
人会有死敌吗？
Do people have arch-enemies?

862
00:44:02,500 --> 00:44:04,190
他是不是给你钱来监视我？
Did he offer you money to spy on me?

863
00:44:05,310 --> 00:44:06,910
- 是的  - 你收了吗？
- Yes. - Did you take it?

864
00:44:07,710 --> 00:44:08,410
没
No.

865
00:44:08,420 --> 00:44:10,230
可惜，我们可以把钱分了，下次要三思
Pity, we could have split the fee. Think it through next time.

866
00:44:11,860 --> 00:44:12,590
他是谁？
Who is he?

867
00:44:12,620 --> 00:44:15,310
你见过的最危险人物 但不是我现在的问题
The most dangerous man you've ever met and not my problem right now.

868
00:44:15,340 --> 00:44:17,030
我桌上 手机号
On my desk, the number!

869
00:44:23,920 --> 00:44:26,190
詹妮弗·威尔逊，这是...
Jennifer Wilson. That was...

870
00:44:26,350 --> 00:44:28,230
等等，这不是那个女死者吗
Hang on. Wasn't that the dead woman?

871
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:31,000
是的，这不重要，输这个号码就好
Yes. That's not important. Just enter the number.

872
00:44:31,430 --> 00:44:32,880
- 你在输吗  - 对
- Are you doing it? - Yes.

873
00:44:33,080 --> 00:44:36,040
- 输完了吗  - 是的，等等
- Have you done it? - Yeah, hang on!

874
00:44:36,530 --> 00:44:38,750
一字不差输这些
These words exactly.

875
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:42,230
“劳瑞斯顿花园发生了什么事
"What happened at Lauriston Gardens?

876
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:44,030
我一定是昏过去了
"I must have blacked out.

877
00:44:44,120 --> 00:44:47,630
诺森伯兰大街22号  请快过来”
"22 Northumberland Street, please come."

878
00:44:47,720 --> 00:44:51,110
- 你昏过去了吗  - 什么？没有...没有
- You blacked out? - What? No... No!

879
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:54,870
输入然后发送 快
Type and send it. Quickly.

880
00:44:59,260 --> 00:45:00,870
- 发送了吗  - 地址是？
- Have you sent it? - What's the address?

881
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:03,310
诺森伯兰大街22号  赶紧的
22 Northumberland Street. Hurry up!

882
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:11,870
这是...
That's...

883
00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:15,940
这是粉衣女士的箱子，詹妮弗·威尔逊的箱子
That's the pink lady's case, that's Jennifer Wilson's case.

884
00:45:15,950 --> 00:45:17,150
是的，显然
Yes, obviously.

885
00:45:19,920 --> 00:45:22,990
也许我该提一下  我没杀她
Oh, perhaps I should mention - I didn't kill her.

886
00:45:23,020 --> 00:45:24,340
- 我从没说是你  - 为什么不是
- I never said you did. - Why not?

887
00:45:24,350 --> 00:45:26,510
鉴于我刚让你发的那短信，而我事实上又有她的箱子
Given that text I just had you send and the fact I have her case,

888
00:45:26,520 --> 00:45:28,210
这是完全合乎逻辑的假设
it's a perfectly logical assumption.

889
00:45:28,220 --> 00:45:30,310
人们通常把你看成凶手吗
Do people usually assume you're the murderer?

890
00:45:31,750 --> 00:45:32,950
时不时会
Now and then, yes.

891
00:45:34,360 --> 00:45:35,550
好吧
Ok...

892
00:45:37,600 --> 00:45:39,670
- 你从哪弄来的？  - 找到的
- How did you get this? - By looking.

893
00:45:39,860 --> 00:45:40,710
哪里
Where?

894
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:42,660
凶手一定是开车带她到劳瑞斯顿花园
The killer must have driven her to Lauriston Gardens.

895
00:45:42,900 --> 00:45:45,390
他碰巧留下箱子只可能是因为它在车里
He could only keep her case by accident if it was in a car.

896
00:45:45,550 --> 00:45:48,400
没人能带着这箱子而不引人注目
Nobody could be seen with this case without drawing attention to himself

897
00:45:48,410 --> 00:45:51,110
尤其是男人 这在统计学上更可能
particularly a man, which is statistically more likely.

898
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:54,270
所以显然 当他发现箱子还在 就急着处理掉它
So obviously he'd feel compelled to get rid of it with he noticed that he still had it

899
00:45:54,280 --> 00:45:56,830
用不了五分钟 他就意识到自己的错误
Wouldn't have taken him more than five minutes to realise his mistake

900
00:45:57,600 --> 00:46:01,350
我检查了劳瑞斯顿花园五分钟车程内每一条后巷
I checked every backstreet wide enough for a car five minutes from Lauriston Gardens

901
00:46:01,360 --> 00:46:04,750
以及任何能不引起注意处理掉大件物品的地方
and anywhere you could dispose of a bulky object without being observed.

902
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:09,100
花了不到一小时就找到了
Took me less than an hour to find the right skip.

903
00:46:10,680 --> 00:46:13,780
粉色，你推论出一切，就因为你认识到箱子会是粉色的吗
Pink. You got all that because you realised the case would be pink?

904
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:15,970
- 必须是粉色，显然  - 我怎么没想到
- It had to be pink, obviously. - Why didn't I think of that

905
00:46:15,980 --> 00:46:17,030
因为你是傻瓜
Because you're an idiot.

906
00:46:17,370 --> 00:46:19,600
不不，别这副表情，实际上人人都是
No, no, don't look like that. Practically everyone is.

907
00:46:20,220 --> 00:46:22,760
现在看看  你发现少了什么吗
Now, look. Do you see what's missing?

908
00:46:22,770 --> 00:46:24,150
箱子里吗？我怎么知道？
From the case? How could I?

909
00:46:25,100 --> 00:46:27,020
她的电话  她的手机在哪里？
Her phone. Where's her mobile phone?

910
00:46:27,030 --> 00:46:28,800
死者身上没手机  箱子里没有手机
There was no phone on the body, there's no phone in the case.

911
00:46:28,810 --> 00:46:31,110
我们知道她有，就是你刚发短信的那个
We know she had one. That's the one there you just texted it.

912
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:32,190
也许她落在家里了
Maybe she left it at home.

913
00:46:32,520 --> 00:46:34,830
她有一串情人  她对此很小心
She has a string of lovers and she's careful about it.

914
00:46:34,840 --> 00:46:37,100
绝不会把手机落在家里
She never leaves her phone at home.

915
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:41,910
那我刚才发短信干嘛？
Er... Why did I just send that text?

916
00:46:42,720 --> 00:46:45,430
问题是，她的手机现在哪里？
Well, the question is where is her phone now?

917
00:46:45,820 --> 00:46:47,910
- 她可能弄丢了  - 对，或者？
- She could have lost it. - Yes, or?

918
00:46:49,970 --> 00:46:52,000
那个凶手，你认为凶手拿着手机？
The murderer... You think the murderer has the phone?

919
00:46:52,840 --> 00:46:56,160
也许她…把手机连同箱子落在车里
Maybe she...left it when she left her case.

920
00:46:56,170 --> 00:46:58,440
也许他出于某种原因拿走了
Maybe he took it from her for some reason.

921
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:02,140
不管哪种，机率上倾向于凶手拿着她的手机
Either way, the balance of probability is the murderer has her phone.

922
00:47:02,150 --> 00:47:04,190
抱歉…我们在做什么？
Sorry...what are we doing?

923
00:47:04,200 --> 00:47:07,030
我刚才是不是给凶手发短信了？这么做有何好处？
Did I just text a murderer? What good will that do?

924
00:47:10,100 --> 00:47:12,080
距离上一个受害者才几小时
A few hours after his last victim,

925
00:47:12,100 --> 00:47:15,590
而现在他收到只可能来自她的短信
and now he receives a text that can only be from her.

926
00:47:17,200 --> 00:47:19,840
如果只是某人捡到那手机，会忽略那样一条短信
If somebody had just found that phone, they'd ignore a text like that,

927
00:47:19,850 --> 00:47:21,410
但那个凶手…
but the murderer...

928
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:23,410
会惊慌
would panic.

929
00:47:26,440 --> 00:47:27,730
你告诉警方了吗？
Have you talked to the police?

930
00:47:27,730 --> 00:47:29,570
已有四人遇害  没时间告诉警方
Four people are dead, there isn't time to talk to the police

931
00:47:29,580 --> 00:47:31,110
那你为何告诉我？
So why are you talking to me?

932
00:47:31,200 --> 00:47:32,950
哈德森太太拿走了我的骷髅
Mrs Hudson took my skull.

933
00:47:34,420 --> 00:47:36,210
所以我主要是填补你的骷髅空虚？
So I'm basically filling in for your skull?

934
00:47:36,220 --> 00:47:37,700
放心，你做得不错
Relax, you're doing fine.

935
00:47:38,200 --> 00:47:39,830
- 那么…  - 那么什么？
- Well? - Well, what?

936
00:47:39,920 --> 00:47:42,840
那么，你可以坐在那儿，看电视
Well...you could just sit there and...watch telly.

937
00:47:42,850 --> 00:47:43,930
你要我跟你去吗？
You want me to come with you?

938
00:47:43,940 --> 00:47:47,300
我出门喜欢有个伴，而且我大声说话时思考更佳
I like company when I go out and I think better when I talk aloud.

939
00:47:47,320 --> 00:47:49,710
骷髅只会引人注目，所以…
The skull just attracts attention, so...

940
00:47:50,470 --> 00:47:51,330
有问题？
Problem?

941
00:47:51,800 --> 00:47:53,000
对，多诺万警佐
Yeah, Sergeant Donovan.

942
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:53,990
她怎么了
What about her?

943
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:57,390
她说，你沉迷于此，你享受其中
She said you get off on this, you enjoy it.

944
00:47:58,400 --> 00:48:01,950
我也说过“有危险”  你也来了
And I said "Dangerous", and here you are.

945
00:48:05,820 --> 00:48:07,070
该死
Damn it!

946
00:48:16,220 --> 00:48:17,100
我们现在去哪里？
Where are we going?

947
00:48:17,480 --> 00:48:19,460
诺森伯兰街，从这走路五分钟
Northumberland Street's a five-minute walk from here.

948
00:48:19,470 --> 00:48:21,020
你真认为他会蠢到去那里吗？
You think he's stupid enough to go there?

949
00:48:21,040 --> 00:48:22,910
不，我认为他够聪明
No, I think he's brilliant enough.

950
00:48:22,970 --> 00:48:24,110
我爱那些聪明的
I love the brilliant ones.

951
00:48:24,120 --> 00:48:26,030
他们都极其渴望被抓
They're all so desperate to get caught.

952
00:48:26,210 --> 00:48:28,190
- 为什么？  - 赞赏
- Why? - Appreciation!

953
00:48:28,280 --> 00:48:30,830
喝彩！ 最终成为焦点人物
Applause! At long last the spotlight.

954
00:48:31,420 --> 00:48:33,630
那是天才们的弱点，约翰，需要一个观众
That's the frailty of genius, John, it needs an audience.

955
00:48:33,900 --> 00:48:34,750
是啊
Yeah.

956
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:36,400
这就是他的猎场
This is his hunting ground.

957
00:48:36,600 --> 00:48:38,870
就在这里，在城市的心脏
Right here in the heart of the city.

958
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:40,660
既然我们知道他的受害者是被劫持的
Now that we know his victims were abducted,

959
00:48:40,670 --> 00:48:42,230
这改变了一切
that changes everything.

960
00:48:42,520 --> 00:48:46,200
因为他所有的受害者都消失在闹市街头
Because all of his victims disappeared from busy streets, crowded places,

961
00:48:46,210 --> 00:48:47,310
可没人看见他们消失
but nobody saw them go.

962
00:48:48,520 --> 00:48:51,680
想想，谁是我们即便不认识也信任的人
Think! Who do we trust, even though we don't know them?

963
00:48:51,690 --> 00:48:54,750
谁去哪里都不引人注意？
Who passes unnoticed wherever they go?

964
00:48:55,200 --> 00:48:57,400
谁在人群当中狩猎？
Who hunts in the middle of a crowd?

965
00:48:57,650 --> 00:48:59,000
不知道  谁？
Don't know. Who?

966
00:48:59,500 --> 00:49:01,350
茫无头绪，饿吗？
Haven't the faintest. Hungry?

967
00:49:05,400 --> 00:49:06,630
谢谢，比利
Thank you, Billy.

968
00:49:11,040 --> 00:49:12,710
诺森伯兰街22号
22 Northumberland Street.

969
00:49:12,800 --> 00:49:14,400
留心盯着
Keep your eyes on it.

970
00:49:15,400 --> 00:49:17,990
他不会直接去按门铃，那得疯了才会
He's not just going to ring the doorbell. He'd need to be mad.

971
00:49:18,550 --> 00:49:20,510
他已杀了四个人
He has killed four people.

972
00:49:21,550 --> 00:49:22,470
好吧
Ok.

973
00:49:24,200 --> 00:49:25,450
夏洛克
Sherlock!

974
00:49:25,480 --> 00:49:28,100
菜单上有的，不管你想吃什么，免费
Anything on the menu, whatever you want, free.

975
00:49:28,210 --> 00:49:30,310
店里买单，给你和你的约会对象
On the house, for you and for your date.

976
00:49:30,330 --> 00:49:31,870
- 你想吃东西吗  - 我不是他的对象
- Do you want to eat? - I'm not his date.

977
00:49:32,050 --> 00:49:33,990
这人帮我洗脱了谋杀嫌疑
This man got me off a murder charge.

978
00:49:34,080 --> 00:49:34,990
这位是安杰洛
This is Angelo.

979
00:49:34,990 --> 00:49:37,150
三年前我向雷斯垂德成功证实…
Three years ago, I successful proved to Lestrade,

980
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:38,880
一起恶性三重谋杀案发生时
at the time of a particularly vicious triple murder,

981
00:49:38,890 --> 00:49:41,950
安杰洛正在城里别的地方，入室行劫
that Angelo was in a different part of town, house-breaking.

982
00:49:41,970 --> 00:49:44,020
- 他清洗了我的名誉  - 我洗刷了一点
- He cleared my name. - I cleared it a bit.

983
00:49:44,030 --> 00:49:45,340
对街有情况吗
Anything happening opposite?

984
00:49:45,350 --> 00:49:46,470
没有
Nothing.

985
00:49:46,480 --> 00:49:48,330
要不是这个人，我就得进监狱了
But for this man, I'd have gone to prison.

986
00:49:48,340 --> 00:49:49,420
你是进了监狱
You did go to prison.

987
00:49:49,420 --> 00:49:52,110
我拿支蜡烛放桌上，更浪漫点
I'll get a candle for the table. It's more romantic.

988
00:49:52,170 --> 00:49:53,590
我不是他对象
I'm not his date!

989
00:49:55,700 --> 00:49:58,470
你最好吃点  我们可能得等很久
You may as well eat. We might have a long wait.

990
00:49:59,620 --> 00:50:00,990
谢谢
Thanks.

991
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:10,110
一般人没有死敌
People don't have arch-enemies.

992
00:50:11,470 --> 00:50:13,110
- 说啥？  - 在现实生活中
- I'm sorry? - In real life.

993
00:50:14,120 --> 00:50:16,680
现实中不存在死敌  没这种事
There are no arch-enemies in real life. Doesn't happen.

994
00:50:16,710 --> 00:50:18,980
没有吗？ 听起来有点闷
Doesn't it? Sounds a bit dull.

995
00:50:19,320 --> 00:50:20,930
所以我遇见了谁？
So who did I meet?

996
00:50:20,970 --> 00:50:24,710
那么常人有什么，在“真实生活”中
What do real people have, then, in their..."real lives"?

997
00:50:25,720 --> 00:50:27,070
朋友？
Friends?

998
00:50:27,160 --> 00:50:30,550
认识的人  喜欢的人  不喜欢的人
People they know, people they like, people they don't like...

999
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:35,270
- 女朋友或男朋友  - 对，正如我所说 闷
- Girlfriends, boyfriends. - Yes, well, as I was saying, dull.

1000
00:50:35,850 --> 00:50:37,200
这么说你没有女朋友？
You don't have a girlfriend, then?

1001
00:50:37,660 --> 00:50:40,110
女朋友？没有，算不上是我的范畴
Girlfriend? No, not really my area.

1002
00:50:42,700 --> 00:50:44,030
哦，好吧
Mm. Oh, right.

1003
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:47,760
那你有男朋友吗？这其实也没关系
Do you have a boyfriend? Which is fine, by the way.

1004
00:50:47,770 --> 00:50:49,300
我知道没关系
I know it's fine.

1005
00:50:51,250 --> 00:50:52,700
- 那你有男朋友？  - 没有
- So you've got a boyfriend, then. - No.

1006
00:50:53,000 --> 00:50:55,100
好的  懂了
Right. OK.

1007
00:50:56,380 --> 00:50:59,030
你是独一个 跟我一样
You're unattached. Like me.

1008
00:50:59,960 --> 00:51:02,250
好  不错
Fine. Good.

1009
00:51:09,920 --> 00:51:12,780
约翰…我想你应该了解
John, um...I think you should know

1010
00:51:12,800 --> 00:51:15,400
我当自己与工作结婚了  虽然我受宠若惊
I consider myself married to my work and while I'm flattered,

1011
00:51:15,410 --> 00:51:19,680
- 但是我真的不是要找...  - 不  我不是在问  不
- I'm really not looking for any... - No, I'm...not asking. No.

1012
00:51:21,080 --> 00:51:24,030
我只是在说  全都没关系
I'm just saying, it's all fine.

1013
00:51:26,320 --> 00:51:27,430
很好
Good.

1014
00:51:29,160 --> 00:51:30,350
谢谢你
Thank you.

1015
00:51:32,300 --> 00:51:35,540
看对街 出租车 停下了
Look across the street. Taxi. It's stopped.

1016
00:51:35,630 --> 00:51:37,390
没人上车  也没人下车
Nobody getting in and nobody getting out.

1017
00:51:38,450 --> 00:51:39,700
为什么是出租车？
Why a taxi?

1018
00:51:40,720 --> 00:51:42,100
哦，聪明啊
Oh, that's clever.

1019
00:51:42,120 --> 00:51:44,210
- 这样聪明吗？这样为什么聪明？  - 那是他？
- Is it clever? Why is it clever? - That's him.

1020
00:51:44,600 --> 00:51:46,510
- 别盯着看  - 你也在盯着
- Don't stare. - You're staring.

1021
00:51:46,900 --> 00:51:48,500
咱俩不能都盯着
We can't both stare.

1022
00:52:12,210 --> 00:52:13,630
抱歉
Sorry...

1023
00:52:14,280 --> 00:52:16,350
- 我记下车牌号码了  - 做得好
- I've got the cab number. - Good for you.

1024
